        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-16T09:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-16T09:15:00-05:00" n="72"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Secretary’s Staff Meetings, lot 63 D 75</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Notes of the Secretary’s Staff Meeting, Held at the Department
                        of State, 9:15 a.m., February 16, 1954</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d72fn1">During the period 1952–1960, the Secretary’s staff
                        meeting met twice a week. The meetings were attended by the Under Secretary
                        of State, Assistant Secretary of State, certain members of the Executive
                        Secretariat, and certain office directors. A broad range of matters was
                        discussed; the Secretary normally presided.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/> SM N–206</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-16T09:15:00-05:00">February 16,
                            1954, 9:15 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follow a list of those present (24) and discussion of matters unrelated to
                    the Tenth Inter-American Conference.]</p>
                <pb facs="0337" n="299" xml:id="pg_299"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Caracas Conference</hi>
                </p>
                <p>2. The Acting Secretary directed Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CJM1"
                    >Cabot</persName>, if approached by Treasury officials, to take the line that
                    what is wanted is a positive statement as to what the Export–Import Bank can do
                    for Latin America on a “yes” rather than “no” basis.</p>
                <p>The Acting Secretary further instructed Mr. <persName corresp="#p_NFE1"
                        >Nolting</persName> to attempt to obtain an assurance from Budget that we
                    would be able to make a statement before or at a Caracas conference in
                    connection with the <persName>Eisenhower</persName> “package proposal.”<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d72fn2">The Secretary’s Mar. 4 address at Caracas contained a
                        reference to the “package proposal” and a statement concerning Export–Import
                        Bank policy. See footnote 14, <ref target="#pg_295">p. 295</ref>.</note> The
                    Acting Secretary added that he felt Budget would be cooperative.</p>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of additional matters unrelated to the Tenth
                    Inter-American Conference.]</p>
            </div>
